{"word":"πειράζω","slug":"πειράζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πειράζω</b></el> <el>(πειράζω,) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make proof</i> or <i>trial of</i>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to attempt</i> to do, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>πεπειράσθω</el> <i>let trial be made</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:πειράω'><el>πειράω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to try</i> or <i>tempt</i> a person, <i>put</i> him <i>to the test</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ὁ πειράζων</el> <i>the tempter</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be sorely tempted, to be tempted to sin</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}